JSONPage.tips:
1.Hold down ALT and click label to achieve highlighting
2.Hold down SHIFT and click label to view the JSON path

projectPage.reviewFooterTips:
Only members deploy projects will trigger review
1. Go to the Deploy page for review
2. Push to URL:http(s)://domain?custom-param=1&callback=***
3. Access the callback value
Repeated access callback will only be published once
projectPage.symlinkHeaderTips:
The project synchronize to the specified directory(rsync /symlinkPath), and ln -s projectPath symlinkPath
It can prevent the project from external access that are being synchronized during the process of synchronizing files
projectPage.symlinkFooterTips: If the deployment path already exists on the target server, please delete the directory manually(rm -rf projectPath), otherwise the symlink will fail
projectPage.afterPullScriptTips:
The script that runs on the host server after pull
For example: bash after-pull-script.sh
projectPage.afterDeployScriptTips:
The script that runs on the target server after deploy
For example: bash after-deploy-script.sh
If you need to restart the service, please pay attention to whether you need nohup
projectPage.autoDeployTitle: Deploy trigger: automatically build the release project after certain conditions are met
projectPage.autoDeploySVNTips:
Go to the hook dir in SVN 
Fill in URL http(s)://domian(IP)/deploy/webhook?project_id={projectId} -X POST --header "Content-Type: application/json" --header "X-SVN-Event: push" -d "{ref}"
